Functional Requirements
1.	User Registration & Login
-	System shall allow users to register by providing email, password, and selecting role (Student or Lecturer).
-	System shall display appropriate error messages for invalid registration or login attempts.

2.	Lecturer Assignment Management
-	Lecturers shall create new assignments with title, description, deadline, and attachments.
-	Lecturers shall delete assignments.
-	Lecturers shall view all assignments they have created.

3.	Student Assignment Viewing
-	Students shall view all assignments posted by their lecturers.
-	Students shall filter assignments by status (Pending, Upcoming, Overdue, Completed).

4.	Deadline Reminders
-	System shall send reminders 48 hours before deadline.
-	System shall send reminders 24 hours before deadline.
-	System shall display overdue notification for missed deadline.

5.	Submission Tracking
-	Students shall mark assignments as ‘Completed’ upon submission.
-	Students shall add submission notes (optional).
-	System shall maintain submission history.


6.	Dashboard
-	System shall display summary statics (total assignments, completed, pending).
-	System shall show upcoming deadlines in priority order.

Non-functional Requirements
1.	Security
-	Passwords shall be encrypted using bcrypt.
-	Role-based access control shall prevent unauthorized actions.
-	Session timeout after 1hour of inactivity.

2.	Performance
-	Page load time shall not exceed 5 seconds.
-	System shall support concurrent users (minimum 100 simultaneous users).

3.	Usability
-	Interface shall be intuitive with maximum 3 clicks to access any feature.
-	System shall be responsive across desktop, tablet and mobile devices.

4.	Reliability
-	System uptime shall be 99.5% during academic hours.
-	Data backup shall occur daily.

5.	Scalability
-	Database design shall accommodate up to 10000 users.
